  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening of Comprehensive Repair Processes From Psychosocial Attention, and Implementation of Individual Rehabilitation Measures in Colombia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project contributes to implement a comprehensive individual reparation strategy in Colombia that seeks to assist 20,000 victims of the armed conflict, to deliver rehabilitation and satisfaction measures, as well as actions that contribute to non-repetition, and to the adequate investment of compensation resources, through the principles of differential and psychosocial approach and action without harm. The comprehensive strategy is being implemented through three emotional recovery protocols with differential characteristics: adult protocol; protocol for adolescents; and protocol for girls and boys.</narrative>
  </description>
